RoleDescription:
Manage your own responsibilities and those of the L&amp;D Team;
Support the L&amp;D Manager, as required;
To identify training needs and define schedules as well as implementation methods;
To take high responsibility for training topics assigned and assure professional service is delivered;
To work with requesting managers to find suitable trainers/vendors with effective content and training methods;
To work collaboratively with different business areas (German, India, Singapore, Japan...) and drive learning &amp; development forward according to business needs;
To be involved in training activities including LNA, program design, course delivery, course evaluation
To continually improve and update the processes of training and development strategies;
To manage and liaise directly with external training service providers/vendors;
To understand, manage and propose the training effectiveness measure;
To manage training budget and improve quality process;
To provide comprehensive reports on all training activities;
To actively participate in ad-hoc Learning &amp; Development projects across the organizationBA degree preferred, with a minimum of 4 years experience in training related, IT industry experience will be an advantage.Proven ability to manage and deliver over 100 training topics annually.Experienced in designing and implementing long-term training programs such as development and qualification programs.Skilled in developing and defining competency frameworks.Ability to lead and motivate, handle multiple tasks effectively and analyze dataPreferred experience in training needs assessment, course design, course delivery or course evaluationExcellent communication skills both in English and Vietnamese, be able to work at all levels, well organized and detail oriented;Good interpersonal skills, excellent attitude, can work under high pressure, be able to prioritize workload with good time management;Good negotiation and conflict management skills, pro-activeness, service-excellent mind set and positive thinking;Confident, high energy, enthusiastic and passionate;Strive for continuous improvement, developing people, team work, flexible thinking, building relationships;International exposureWhy BOSCH?Because we do not just follow trends, we create them. Together we turn ideas into reality, working every day to make the world of tomorrow a better place. Do you have high standards when it comes to your job? So do we. At Bosch, you will discover more than just work.Benefits and Career OpportunitiesWorking in one of the Best Places to Work in Vietnam and Top 30 of the Most Innovative Companies all over the worldJoin in a dynamic and fast-growing global company (English-speaking environment), with opportunity to work in global projects and being a part of innovation team contributing initiative ideas to the hi-tech worldOnsite opportunities: short-term and long-term assignments in worldwide officesEngage in our diverse training programs which surely help strengthen both your personal and professionalism13th-month salary bonus + attractive performance bonus (you'll love it!) + annual performance appraisal100% offered salary and mandatory social insurances in 2-month probation15++ days of annual leave + 1-day of birthday leavePremium health insurance for employee and 02 family membersFlexible working time and working modelLunch and parking allowanceGood benefits of company activities such as: football, badminton, yoga, Aerobic, team building...
